JOHANNESBURG - Floyd Shivambu will have to answer to Parliament s Disciplinary Committee.It's for remarks the EFF chief whip made during a no confidence debate in November.During the speech, Shivambu said President Jacob Zuma is a post-colonial disaster.READ: 'You are not my mother,' Shivambu tells MbeteHe also told ANC MPs Zuma would have them arrested and killed if they stood against him.Shivambu was asked to withdraw his comments, but he refused.National Assembly speaker Baleka Mbete has now referred the matter to the committee.eNCA